-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Combined Group of Kuwait, Saudi Cement
-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2012-06-03T13:01:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/persian-gulf-stocks-combined-group-of-kuwait-saudi-cement.html
Saudi Arabia ’s Tadawul All Share
Index gained 1 percent, the most since May 22, to 6,747.69 at
the close in Riyadh. Kuwait’s measure declined 1.2 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Combined Group Contracting Co. (CGC)   fell 3 percent, the
most since May 28, to 1,280 fils. The Kuwaiti construction
company said it plans to challenge a ruling by the Court of
Appeals ordering it to pay U.S.-based EB Holdings Inc. $11.3
million, according to a filing to Kuwait Stock Exchange today.  Saudi Cement Co. (SACCO)   advanced 1.4 percent, the most
since May 22, to 89.25 riyals. The board of the Saudi cement
maker recommended paying a dividend 3.5 riyals a share for the
first half of 2012.  Saudi Cable Co. (SCACO)   climbed 1.7 percent, the most
since May 21, to 15.30 riyals. The company said its Turkish unit
won cable supply order valued at as much as $17 million in
Russia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
